{
  "text": "There are two categories of damage to hydrated DNA resulting from interaction with ionizing radiation. The first is direct-type damage, resulting from direct ionization of the DNA or its inner hydration layer [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The holes and [CITATION_3] Author to whom correspondence should be addressed at Department Biochemistry/Biophysics, University of Rochester Medical Center, 575 Elmwood Ave., Rochester, NY 14642.",
